OL,5, The cost of regulated rail fares in    
OL,6, England will rise by up to 4.9% from   
OL,7, Sunday.                                
OL,9,FThe jump is likely to be unwelcome for 
OL,10,Frail passengers, adding to the rising  
OL,11,Fcost of living seen in recent years. It
OL,12,Falso comes at a time when passengers   
OL,13,Fhave faced disruption to services due  
OL,14,Fto strikes by rail workers over the    
OL,15,Fpast 18 months.                        
OL,17,FTraditionally, fares are hiked based on
OL,18,FJuly's retail prices index measure of  
OL,19,Finflation, which in 2023 was 9%, plus  
OL,20,Fan additional 1%.                      
